quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  21,11,"And how many from a village/urban city We destroyed/broke , (it) was unjust/oppressive, and We created/formed after it a nation (of) others"
  21,12,"So when they felt with one of their physical senses Our might/power , then they are from it running (fleeing)"
  21,13,"Do not run, and return to what you were luxuriated/ungrateful and arrogant in it and your residences, maybe/perhaps you be asked/questioned"
  21,14,"They said: \"Oh our calam ity that we, we were unjust/oppressive"
  21,15,So it was still/continuing that it (was) their call/prayer until We made them uprooted (and) silent/dead
  21,16,And We did not create the skies/space and the earth/Planet Earth and what (is) between them (B) playing/amusing
  21,17,"If We wanted that We take a plaything/an amusement , We would have taken it from at Us, if We were making/doing"
  21,18,"Rather We throw/hurl with the truth on the falsehood, so it nullifies/eliminates it (the falsehood), so then it(the falsehood) is vanishing/being destroyed , and for you (is) the grief/misfortune from what you describe/categorize"
  21,19,"And for Him whom (is) between the skies/space and the earth/Planet Earth, and whom (are) at Him do not be arrogant from worshipping Him, and they do not grieve/sadden"
  21,20,"They praise/glorify (during) the night and the daytime, they do not subside/abate"
  21,21,"Or they took/received gods from the earth/Planet Earth, they are reviving/resurrecting"
  21,22,"If (there) was in them (B) (the skies and the Earth) gods, except God, they (B) would have been corrupted ,so praise/glory (to) God, Lord (of) the throne about what they describe/categorize"
  21,23,"(He is) not to be asked/questioned about what He makes/does, and they are being asked/questioned"
  21,24,"Or they took/received from other than Him gods, say: \"Bring/give your proof/evidence that (is a) reminder/mention what (is) with me, and (a) reminder/mention what (is) before me, but most of them do not know the truth , so they are objecting/opposing"